  <section class="os-episode" id="compensation-pathway" hidden aria-labelledby="episode-title"><div class="shell">
    <div class="os-episode-label"><div><p class="os-eyebrow">FLAGSHIP DECISION EPISODE · PRIMARY DOMAIN: COMPENSATION INTELLIGENCE™</p><h2 id="episode-title">Compensation, made legible.</h2></div><p>Move at the depth you need. Your progress stays private in this browser.</p></div>
    <ol class="os-steps" aria-label="Decision Episode steps"><li class="is-active" data-step="problem">Problem</li><li data-step="context">Context</li><li data-step="big">Big Picture · 30 sec</li><li data-step="brief">Brief Overview · 2 min</li><li data-step="deep">Deep Dive · 5 min</li><li data-step="calculator">Calculator</li><li data-step="checklist">Checklist</li><li data-step="action">Action Plan</li><li data-step="reflection">Reflection</li><li data-step="outcome">OUTCOME</li><li data-step="share">SHARE</li></ol>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="problem"><p class="os-eyebrow">PROBLEM</p><h2>What part of this compensation decision is unclear?</h2><p>Separate the headline number from the formula, terms, and evidence you need before you decide.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="context">Set the context <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="context" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">CONTEXT</p><h2>Use the offer and the work behind it.</h2><p>Keep the written offer, expected workload, attribution rules, and reconciliation schedule in view. They determine whether the number fits your situation.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="big">See the Big Picture · 30 sec <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="big" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">BIG PICTURE · 30 SEC</p><h2>A compensation number is not a compensation formula.</h2><div class="os-formula"><b>YOUR COMPENSATION</b><span>Guarantee</span><i>+</i><span>Productivity</span><i>+</i><span>Quality</span><i>+</i><span>Call / leadership</span><i>−</i><span>Unseen conditions</span></div><div class="os-insights"><p><b>01</b> The headline salary may only be the guarantee.</p><p><b>02</b> Thresholds and attribution determine what work pays.</p><p><b>03</b> Reconciliation tells you whether the formula works in practice.</p></div><div class="os-stat"><strong>One request can change the entire conversation.</strong><span>Ask for the full written formula and two recent reconciliation statements.</span></div><p class="os-transition">You understand the formula. Next, test the offer.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="brief">Continue to Brief Overview · 2 min <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="brief" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">BRIEF OVERVIEW · 2 MIN</p><h2>Same salary. Different economics.</h2><div class="os-offers"><div><span>OFFER A</span><b>$300k</b><p>Clear threshold · Quarterly reconciliation · Defined attribution</p></div><div><span>OFFER B</span><b>$300k</b><p>Higher threshold · Annual reconciliation · Unclear exclusions</p></div></div><div class="os-decision-tree"><h3>Use this decision tree</h3><ol><li><strong>Do you have the complete formula and incorporated policies?</strong> If not, request them before evaluating the offer.</li><li><strong>Can you state the threshold, rate, attribution, timing, and downside in one sentence?</strong> If not, request definitions and a worked example.</li><li><strong>Do low, expected, and high scenarios fit the work and risk you would accept?</strong> If not, clarify or negotiate the assumptions.</li></ol></div><p class="os-action"><strong>Three questions to bring:</strong> What is the exact threshold? What rate applies after it? Which work is credited to me, when, and how can I verify it?</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="deep">Work through the Deep Dive · 5 min <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="deep" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">DEEP DIVE · 5 MIN</p><h2>Turn a number into questions you can use.</h2><div class="os-deep"><div><h3>Stress-test the formula</h3><ol><li>Write the guarantee, unit, threshold, rate, attribution, reconciliation, and downside in one sentence.</li><li>Test low, expected, and high activity—not only the employer’s target.</li><li>Ask what happens to late claims, denials, corrections, APP work, multiple sites, leave, and global periods.</li><li>Separate cash pay from retirement, insurance, CME, tail, call, schedule control, and contractor expenses.</li></ol></div><div><h3>Common mistakes</h3><ul><li>Comparing guarantees without workload.</li><li>Treating an employer wRVU rate as CMS reimbursement.</li><li>Missing attribution leakage or capacity constraints.</li><li>Ignoring a draw, deficit carry-forward, clawback, or plan-amendment right.</li><li>Comparing W-2 and 1099 income without expenses, benefits, and fact-specific classification review.</li></ul></div></div><details class="os-faq"><summary>FAQ: When should I ask for professional review?</summary><p>Seek legal review for unclear restrictive covenants, termination, repayment, amendment, ownership, or referral-sensitive terms. Seek tax, accounting, benefits, or valuation advice when structure, timing, benefits, fair-market-value, or compliance questions are material. This framework helps you organize facts; it does not replace individualized advice.</p></details><p class="os-transition">You now have the framework. Put your assumptions into a visible formula.</p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="calculator">Open the scenario calculator <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="calculator" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">INTERACTIVE CALCULATOR</p><h2>Make the formula visible.</h2><p class="os-panel-intro">Change one assumption at a time. The interpretation updates immediately; it is an illustration, not a valuation.</p><div class="os-calculator"><label>Guaranteed compensation <small>Fixed cash for the period entered.</small><input data-calc="guarantee" type="number" value="300000" min="0"></label><label>Credited activity <small>wRVUs or the unit named in your plan.</small><input data-calc="units" type="number" value="6000" min="0"></label><label>Productivity threshold <small>Units before the productivity rate applies.</small><input data-calc="threshold" type="number" value="5000" min="0"></label><label>Productivity rate per unit <input data-calc="factor" type="number" value="55" min="0"></label><label>Quality adjustment <input data-calc="quality" type="number" value="0" min="0"></label><label>Call, leadership, teaching, other cash <input data-calc="additional" type="number" value="0" min="0"></label><label>Benefits value you enter <input data-calc="benefits" type="number" value="0" min="0"></label><label>Expenses, draw repayment, or clawback risk <input data-calc="risk" type="number" value="0" min="0"></label><output data-calculator-result aria-live="polite">Illustrative value: $355,000</output><p class="os-calculator-interpretation" data-calculator-interpretation aria-live="polite"></p><p class="os-calculator-trace" data-calculator-trace>Formula trace: guarantee + payable activity × rate + quality + additional pay + benefits − entered risk.</p><div class="os-tool-actions"><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-calculator-save>Save this scenario privately</button><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-calculator-export>Copy scenario summary</button><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-calculator-compare>Compare low / expected / high</button></div><output class="os-scenario-comparison" data-scenario-comparison aria-live="polite"></output><details class="os-assumptions"><summary>Assumptions and limits</summary><p>Productivity pay is calculated only on activity above the threshold. Benefits and risk are values you enter; the tool does not infer them. Confirm the unit, timing, attribution, exclusions, tiers, and repayment treatment in the written plan.</p></details><small>Educational illustration only. You supply the assumptions. This does not determine fair market value, legal compliance, tax treatment, worker classification, or the correct offer.</small></div><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="checklist">Open the downloadable checklist <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="checklist" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">DOWNLOADABLE CHECKLIST</p><h2>Leave with a clear request.</h2><p class="os-panel-intro">Use this as a conversation-ready agenda. Checks stay in this browser.</p><div data-print-checklist><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Complete written formula and every incorporated policy received.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Guarantee duration, transition, draw, deficit, and repayment treatment defined.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Unit, threshold, rate, tiers, caps, floors, and exclusions defined.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Attribution, APP, site, late-claim, denial, and correction rules defined.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Schedule, call, sites, supervision, leave, and administrative work compared.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Quality, call, leadership, teaching, and other compensation addressed.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Reconciliation schedule, data access, correction window, and dispute path confirmed.</label><label class="os-check"><input type="checkbox" data-action-check> Benefits, expenses, malpractice/tail, and contractor costs valued separately.</label></div><div class="os-tool-actions"><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-checklist-download>Print / save PDF checklist</button><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-checklist-copy>Copy checklist</button><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-question-sheet>Print employer question sheet</button></div><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="action">Build my action plan <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="action" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">ACTION PLAN</p><h2>Your next conversation, prepared.</h2><div class="os-script-grid"><section><h3>Open the meeting</h3><p class="os-quote">“I want to understand the formula and workload behind this offer before I evaluate the total package.”</p></section><section><h3>Ask in writing</h3><p class="os-quote">“Please provide the productivity formula, threshold, conversion factor, attribution rules, quality measures, and reconciliation schedule in writing.”</p></section><section><h3>Avoid leading with</h3><p>“What is everyone else making?” Ask instead for the plan definitions, a role-specific worked example, and how you can verify credited work.</p></section></div><details class="os-assumptions"><summary>Copy-ready follow-up email</summary><p>Thank you for discussing the role. To compare the offer accurately, please send the complete compensation plan and incorporated policies, including the guarantee, productivity measure and threshold, rate or tiers, attribution, quality terms, call or leadership pay, reconciliation timing, and any draw, repayment, clawback, or amendment provisions. I would also appreciate a worked example using the expected workload for this role.</p><button type="button" class="os-text-link" data-email-copy>Copy email template</button></details><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="reflection">Record your confidence <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="reflection" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">REFLECTION</p><h2>What changed in your understanding?</h2><p>Save a private confidence check. It is stored only in this browser.</p><div class="os-confidence" data-confidence-options aria-label="Confidence from zero to ten"></div><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="outcome">See your Decision Win <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
    <article class="os-panel" data-panel="outcome" hidden><p class="os-eyebrow">YOUR DECISION WIN</p><h2>You now know exactly what compensation formula to request.</h2><div class="os-decision-win"><span>✓</span><p>Estimated impact: <strong>a more informed compensation conversation.</strong><br><small>The next step is a better question, not a promised result.</small></p></div><div class="os-outcome-capture"><p><strong>Private progress check</strong> — local to this browser only. Do not add employer, contract, or offer details.</p><label>Planned action <select data-planned-action><option value="">Choose one</option><option>Request the written formula</option><option>Run scenarios before meeting</option><option>Ask for professional review</option><option>Revisit after my meeting</option></select></label><label>Return reminder <select data-return-reminder><option value="">No reminder</option><option value="3">In 3 days</option><option value="7">In 1 week</option><option value="14">In 2 weeks</option></select></label><label>Brief reflection <textarea data-outcome-reflection rows="2" maxlength="280" placeholder="What will you clarify next? Keep it non-identifying."></textarea></label><label class="os-consent"><input type="checkbox" data-outcome-consent> I understand this is an optional, local-only reflection.</label><button type="button" data-outcome="helpful" disabled>More confident</button><button type="button" data-outcome="revisit" disabled>Need to revisit</button><p data-outcome-progress aria-live="polite"></p><button type="button" class="os-button" data-clear-local-progress>Clear my saved local progress</button><p><small>A selected return date is stored only in this browser. It does not create a notification or reminder.</small></p></div><button type="button" class="os-button" data-next="share">Help a colleague <span aria-hidden="true">→</span></button></article>
